editorialSummary.text: Contemporary coffeehouse offering Asian donuts, waffles, matcha lattes, teas, and espresso drinks.

originalText.text: This bubble tea spot was super busy when we got there but luckily the seating area is quite big and very nicely decorated. They have a good selection of drinks and also dessert items. They have these delicious shaved ice cream desserts that look like sundaes. They are huge! Definitely worth the wait and the experience. I would definitely come by again when I visit Koreatown.

originalText.text: Amidst the lively atmosphere, this spot stands out with its delectable sweets. From the moment you step in, the enticing aroma of freshly made treats fills the air. Despite the constant flow of customers, the service remains efficient and friendly. The menu showcases a diverse range of desserts, each offering a unique twist on traditional Korean flavors. This place is a sweet escape in the heart of Manhattan's Ktown. Embrace the crowds and treat yourself! But be warned that finding a seat is quite difficult.

originalText.text: Always very very busy. And tightly packed.. No awards for comfort... But definitely tasty and creative treats. We had waffles with bananas and strawberries and shaved ice. They have you order now at the entrance, presumably to speed up the whole process. You pick up your order when buzzed... so not exactly any service... Can be tough finding a seat if more than two people... Walking up and down aisles to find a place....The seating should be done better....have the staff help out. It used to be better. It now feels like I should receive a W2 for doing a lot of work. 40 bucks for those and a tea.... Hmmmm.....

originalText.text:
All I can say is WOW! The desserts are as amazing as they look. The basque cheesecake was absolutely delicious. It doesn’t look that good but don’t be fooled by that.

I passed by this place a few months ago and wanted to try it for their shaved ice cream.

So when I got an invite to meet some friends I wasn’t going to pass it up. I met up with the ladies and we ordered a few different desserts. I ordered the mango madness shaved ice cream and the portion was huge. Easily enough for 3 people to share it. It was $20 with a $2 tip which I thought was a little pricey. I shared with one other person and we still had  leftover. The shaved ice cream was a little over average. Another friend ordered Nutella Mochi waffle which I didn’t get to try but it looked incredible. Also really big portion so two people can share it.

They gave us the Ho-Dduks with ice cream on the house which was really nice of them and those were out of this world. They had a creamy hazelnut filling and were warm which paired well with the ice cream. Another friend order the lavender tea which looked delicious and she said it was pretty good.

I got there around 6pm on a Saturday and there was only 4 people ahead of me in line. We ended up leaving at 9pm and there were about 30 people on line but I get the hype. It’s worth it for sure.

The inside is massive with plenty of seating.
I’m going to go back for the Nutella mochi waffles :)

originalText.text: An absolute gem in the heart of ktown, this dessert spot is a perfect place to visit after dining at any of the other neighboring restaurants. Don’t be fooled by the long lines, as the inside is huge and the line moves pretty fast. My favorite dessert item is the Ho-Dduk!
